Source: wasta-vertex-ubuntu
Section: utils
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Rik Shaw <rikshaw76@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 8.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: https://github.com/wasta-linux/wasta-vertex-ubuntu

Package: wasta-vertex-ubuntu
Architecture: all
Depends: humanity-colors, ubuntu-mono, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Wasta-Vertex Ubuntu Icons
 Thanks to horst3180 for his great vertex-icons icon theme.  Original source
 found here: https://github.com/horst3180/Vertex-icons.  Wasta-Vertex uses
 the vertex-icons folder icons for larger sizes but modifies the 16/22/24 px
 folder icons.  All other icons are inherited by "Humanity Dark Aqua Tru"
 which is the ubuntu-mono-dark theme modified to use an aqua instead of
 Ubuntu's standard "orange".  The inherited theme can be changed in the
 index.theme file.
